 habitational name from Walford in Wimborne Minster (Dorset). The placename probably derives from Old English <i>walt</i> ‘unsteady’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Hugo","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized form of   Hugh  , used throughout the Middle Ages in official documents, and now enjoying a revival as a given name."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Hugo De Walford was born in 1140, in Walford, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir Hugo de WALFORD, was 25 and his mother, Mrs Hugo De Walford, was 22. He married Mrs Hugo De Walford about 1169, in Walford, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died after 1200, in England, United Kingdom, and was buried in Walford, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1140–after 1200":"1140–pärast 1200","1140–1200":"1140–1200","1145–Female":"1145–Surnud","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","1175–1240":"1175–1240","1178–Male":"1178–Surnud","1115–Male":"1115–Surnud","1119–Female":"1119–Surnud","about 1170":"umbes 1170","1175":"1175","1240":"1240","1140":"1140","1170":"1170","1115":"1115","1178":"1178","1145":"1145","1200":"1200","about 1139":"umbes 1139","about 1169":"umbes 1169","about 1178":"umbes 1178","after 1200":"pärast 1200","about 1175":"umbes 1175","1119":"1119","Walford, Herefordshire, England":"Walford, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1140–after 1200":"1140–1200 jälkeen","1140–1200":"1140–1200","1145–Female":"1145–Kuollut","1170–Male":"1170–Kuollut","1175–1240":"1175–1240","1178–Male":"1178–Kuollut","1115–Male":"1115–Kuollut","1119–Female":"1119–Kuollut","about 1170":"noin 1170","1175":"1175","1240":"1240","1140":"1140","1170":"1170","1115":"1115","1178":"1178","1145":"1145","1200":"1200","about 1139":"noin 1139","about 1169":"noin 1169","about 1178":"noin 1178","after 1200":"1200 jälkee